column5: I have had to log in here three times so far today! I log in, all is well, then, for no reason I can see, I find, myself no longer logged in. I do click the "remember me" button but I still find that I am getting kicked out. Anyone provide some ideas as to why?  Thanks,  HH
Your computer has Altzheimers, get it a prescription for  AriceptÂ®!!!!
Are you at work? We are using new cookies here. If i takes you a loooong time to read a page u may be timing out your session...but that has not happened to me. Anyone else get that problem?

Rick, yes I am at work and I'm beginning to think that it is timing out. I have had to once again, login after about an hour away from the board... so is this possibly the answer, timing out? I know I had not logged out yet... HH
I had the same problem last night kept logging in; log in sucessful but not logged in.after several hours I was finally able to log in.  MTP
I told you it wouldn't work and they would just keep trying     LOL
Jeez, a man complaining of being blown out, go figure
Maybe it is a subtle hint......

Ok... so after feeling completely spent after being "blown out" four times today, I chrushed a viagra on my key board. I don't know if it will help me stay logged in, but ALL OF A SUDDEN I DON'T NEED TO PUSH THE CAPS LOCK BUTTON ANYMORE!  HH
